WASHINGTON, September 10 (Xinhua)--Tropical storm Floyd strengthened Friday to become the fourth Atlantic hurricane this year, moving through the north Atlantic on a path that will take it north of the Caribbean islands and toward the eastern United States.
 At 14:00 GMT, the center of the hurricane was about 330 kilometers east-northeast of Barbuda at latitude 19.1 north, longitude 58.9 west, the NHC said.